§7§oThis gate works like an AND gate, but it can also mantain one of the input signals.

The output is the side with the taller torch.

The strong input is the side with the shorter torch.

The top line connects the other two sides.

The top line can act as a redstone line, transmitting signals to the other side.

If both the strong input, and either side of the strong line are on, the output will be on.
